name: Etsy
description: Add an Etsy Instance to connect your existing Etsy account to the eCommerce Hub, allowing you to manage orders and products across multiple eCommerce Elements. You will need your Etsy account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: OAuth Scope
configuration.defaultValue: recommend_rw email_r listings_r listings_w listings_d transactions_r transactions_w cart_rw shops_rw billing_r profile_r profile_w address_r address_w favorites_rw feedback_r treasury_r treasury_w

configuration.name: Max Page Size (or limit)
configuration.description: Etsy Beta Max Page Size (or limit)

configuration.name: The Shop ID
configuration.description: The shop id to use in the URL path for API requests.  This can be the numerical shop ID or the name of the shop.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Objects|URL
configuration.description: An element polling Objects and URL used for event notifications from provider, if URL is not mentioned then it uses the default URL for polling for that object, format should be objectname|url

configuration.name: Event Notification Callback URL
configuration.description: Etsy Beta Event Notification Callback URL

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

parameters.name: where

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The customer ID

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. min_created is a mandatory field. Ex:'min_created=1548979200' where the value is in Epoch TimeStamp Format

resources.description: List all orders in the eCommerce system.

parameters.name: Transactions
parameters.description: includes

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. When this parameter is omitted, 1 is implied.

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of results to fetch in a given page with a maximum of 2000. When this parameter is omitted, 200 results are returned.

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for objects where name equals foo, the search expression will be name='foo'. When this parameter is omitted, all objects are returned in a paginated fashion.
